Issue Recap:
DDS failed to parse a BAAD content type file during processing. Initial review indicates the parser is encountering an incomplete end-of-file marker while reading the file buffer, causing the file to fail parsing. This appears related to how DDS processes larger files where the parser reads only a partial segment and does not detect a full file termination.

Services/Applications Impacted:
DDS File Processing – BAAD content type ingestion.

Business/Customer Impact:
BAAD file content is currently not being successfully processed by DDS. This may delay ingestion of BAAD records until the file is resent or processed through a workaround.

Next Steps:
Engineering is investigating the parsing failure and validating whether splitting the file into smaller segments and resending will allow DDS to successfully parse the content. A technical incident call will be initiated if further coordination is required.